From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000009 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESP32-S3 Web Simulator contributors <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 19:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] esp32s3: model Cardputer ADV IMU and battery ADC

Attach the Cardputer ADV BMI270 to its internal I2C bus and add the
ESP32-S3 RTC one-shot SAR ADC path used to sample the GPIO10 battery
divider. Expose the ADC input through QOM so the worker can inject
deterministic battery voltage through the normal firmware path.
---
 hw/adc/Kconfig                    |   3 +
 hw/adc/esp32s3_saradc.c           | 210 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 hw/adc/meson.build                |   1 +
 hw/nvram/esp32s3_efuse.c          |   9 ++
 hw/xtensa/Kconfig                 |   1 +
 hw/xtensa/esp32s3.c               |  18 +++
 include/hw/adc/esp32s3_saradc.h   |  30 +++++
 7 files changed, 272 insertions(+)

diff --git a/hw/adc/Kconfig b/hw/adc/Kconfig
index 25d2229fb83b25cac03b49ef56e4aa0ae1af1190..2efad6f1be6558e2d9b71cf7ef916137866bfd5f 100644
--- a/hw/adc/Kconfig
+++ b/hw/adc/Kconfig
@@ -1,2 +1,5 @@
 config STM32F2XX_ADC
